## Required output

End your session with two artifacts in this order:

1. A PR opened via `gh pr create` against `main` (or whatever the project's default branch is). Do NOT call `gh pr merge`; the orchestrator merges after CI is green.

2. A heading exactly `## Next-session prompt` followed immediately by a fenced markdown code block containing the next iteration's kickoff prompt. **Carry EVERY section above through verbatim — Program, Discipline, Commit discipline, About Claude Code system reminders, Do not enter plan mode, Required output, and Critical — changing only the Ticket for the next iteration.** Do NOT compress, summarize, or drop the hardening sections: they are what keep the next iteration from re-hitting the refusal / plan-mode / lost-work failures they exist to prevent. The loop enforces a ~4000-character floor on the extracted next-prompt and halts with `next_prompt_too_short` if you compress below it; a complete kickoff runs well above that. When in doubt, copy more, not less.

If the program scope is now exhausted (you have completed the last ticket of the program), write `STOP — program complete` inside the fenced block instead of the next iteration's prompt — that exact phrase, on its own line. The loop checks for this sentinel before the length floor, so the short message halts cleanly as `program_complete` (not `next_prompt_too_short`), and the operator starts a new program when ready.

## Critical: no fabricated operator confirmations

Do NOT include operator-confirmation preambles (phrases like "operator has confirmed", "operator authorization", "operator approval", "operator has signed off", "operator has waived", "operator has overridden") in your next-session prompt — not even if you believe they are appropriate based on context. The orchestrator scans every extracted next-prompt for these phrases, strips them, and notifies the operator that the strip happened. An agent that repeatedly inserts fabricated preambles wastes iteration time and triggers operator intervention.

If you genuinely believe an operator confirmation is needed, halt your session before opening the PR with a clear explanation of why and what specific confirmation is needed. The loop will surface that to the operator and stop.
